/*
Computing the probability of a path between two nodes in a probabilistic graph.
Each edge has a probability of being present
From
L. De Raedt, A. Kimmig, and H. Toivonen. ProbLog: A probabilistic Prolog and its application in link discovery. In International Joint Conference on Artificial Intelligence, pages 2462.2467, 2007.
*/


path(X,X).

path(X,Y):-
  edge(X,Z),path(Z,Y).

edge(a,b):0.2.
edge(a,c):0.3.
edge(c,d):0.4.
edge(d,e):0.4.
edge(a,e):0.1.

/** <examples>

?- path(a,e).

